// Man page for exit
manExit="EXIT(1)                          X Shell Manual                          EXIT(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    exit - Exit framework or active session
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>exit</b> [<b>-y</b>|<b>-n</b>]
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Terminates the current session. On main session, prompts if active
    sessions exist. On proxy, prompts for confirmation (use <b>-y</b> or the
    <b>yes</b> command to skip, <b>-n</b> to also skip). On pivot/shell
    sessions, exits immediately.
    Aliases: x
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>exit</b>
    Exit current session (may prompt for confirmation)

    <b>exit -y</b>
    Skip confirmation prompt (or run <b>yes</b> first)

    <b>exit -n</b>
    Skip confirmation prompt (proxy sessions)
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Standard Exit</color>
    <b>exit</b>
    Exit with prompt

    <b>x</b>
    Quick exit alias

    <color=#e4ff34># Proxy Session</color>
    <b>exit -y</b>
    Exit proxy without confirmation

    <b>yes</b>
    <b>exit</b>
    Same via session auto-yes
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>close</b>, <b>home</b>, <b>x</b>, <b>yes</b>"